    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-02T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-02T06:00:00-05:00" n="514"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d514">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.71261/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-02T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 2, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 3—3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>587. Department’s 364, May 26, 8 p.m. I outlined to Molotov the considerations
                    contained in the reference telegram, stressed the desirability of maintaining
                    and improving mail communications between <pb facs="0675" n="663"
                        xml:id="pg_663"/> the United States and the Soviet Union and strongly
                    pressed for an early solution of that problem.<note n="73" xml:id="d514fn73">At
                        times the Soviet Embassy in Washington raised the subject of slowness of
                        transmission of its diplomatic cables to Moscow as sent through commercial
                        companies usually without knowing the nature of the technical difficulties
                        temporarily encountered.</note> I left with him a note on the subject.
                    Molotov stated that he would have the question examined and would communicate
                    again with me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
